---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="Terms of Service — LongevityStack"
      description="Terms of Service for LongevityStack. Rules and conditions for using this website."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>

      <div class="page-header">
        <div class="tag">Legal</div>
        <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
        <div class="meta">Last updated: March 2026</div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose">

        <h2>Acceptance of terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing and using LongevityStack (longevitystack.pages.dev), you accept and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree to these terms, please do not use this site.
        </p>

        <h2>Use of content</h2>
        <p>
          All content on LongevityStack — including articles, protocols, research summaries, and visual elements — is provided for informational and educational purposes only. You may not reproduce, distribute, or commercially exploit any content from this site without explicit written permission.
        </p>
        <p>
          You may share links to articles on this site freely. Brief quotations with proper attribution are permitted under fair use.
        </p>

        <h2>No medical advice</h2>
        <p>
          Nothing on this site constitutes medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment. See our <a href="/medical-disclaimer">Medical Disclaimer</a> for full details. Always consult a qualified healthcare professional before making health-related decisions.
        </p>

        <h2>Affiliate relationships</h2>
        <p>
          LongevityStack participates in affiliate programs. We may earn commissions on purchases made through affiliate links at no cost to you. All affiliate relationships are disclosed inline within each article. Our editorial content is not influenced by affiliate relationships.
        </p>

        <h2>Accuracy of information</h2>
        <p>
          We make every effort to ensure the accuracy of information published on this site. However, we make no warranties or representations regarding the completeness, accuracy, or timeliness of any content. Scientific understanding evolves — information that is accurate today may be revised by future research.
        </p>

        <h2>External links</h2>
        <p>
          This site contains links to external websites, including PubMed, NIH, and product pages. We are not responsible for the content, accuracy, or privacy practices of external sites. Links to external sources do not constitute endorsement.
        </p>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All original content on LongevityStack is the intellectual property of Bernardo Paranhos. The LongevityStack name, logo, and brand elements are proprietary. Unauthorized use is prohibited.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          LongevityStack and its author shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of this site or reliance on any information published here. Use of this site is entirely at your own risk.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to update these Terms of Service at any time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated date. Continued use of the site after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These terms are governed by the laws of Brazil. Any disputes shall be resolved under Brazilian jurisdiction.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about these terms: <a href="mailto:contact@longevitystack.org">contact@longevitystack.org</a>
        </p>

      </div>

    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 28px 80px;
  }
  .page-header {
    padding: 48px 0 32px;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--color-border);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }
  .tag {
    display: inline-block;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 10px;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 4px 12px;
    border-radius: 20px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    letter-spacing: 1px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .meta {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--color-hint);
  }
  .prose h2 {
    font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .prose p {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .prose ul {
    padding-left: 22px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .prose li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .prose a {
    color: var(--color-green);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
</style>